                  <summary>This private letter is entirely concerned with a matter of business. The writer&amp;apos;s attention is concentrated on the need of money to defray expenses and of papyrus for producing accounts, or a register of other official papers. The drift of the text suggests that he is a partner in a small firm of scribes, perhaps a family enterprise, specializing in such work.</summary>
